transcript:
here's a quick tip from a psychologist
self-sabotage is knowing what's best for
you and not doing it every time you
choose a path that's not in your best
interest you are reconfirming your
belief that you don't deserve any better
self-sabotage can be small things like
procrastinating over doing that job that
you know would make your life easier but
it could also be bigger decisions like
staying in relationships that hurt you
but the good news is that self-sabotage
is not who you are it's a pattern that
you've learned over time
and so you can learn new patterns
for more on how to do that check out why
has nobody told me this before
